<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13519] Support coupled compactions with secondary index </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13519</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DELI (DEferred Lightweight Indexing) is our research prototype from Syracuse University with collaboration from Georgia Tech and IBM Research. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In DELI, we propose that when supporting secondary index on HBase, the index-to-base-table sync-up should be coupled with compaction. The benefit of this is that online Put stays to be append-only and performance would be guaranteed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code of DELI is shared in github: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/tristartom/nosql-indexing&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/tristartom/nosql-indexing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details can be found in the following research paper published in CCGrid 2015: &lt;a href=&quot;http://tristartom.github.io/docs/ccgrid15.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://tristartom.github.io/docs/ccgrid15.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are grateful for the HBase community, and any comments/suggestions are appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yuzhe&lt;/p&gt;</description>
