                            <comment id="14506369" author="elserj" created="Wed, 22 Apr 2015 03:54:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tristartom&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tristartom&quot;&gt;tristartom&lt;/a&gt;. I saw that you also made an announcement for this work on the mailing lists. Is this something that you&apos;re planning to integrate with upstream HBase (hence the new feature tag)? Thanks for sharing!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14510461" author="tristartom" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 04:54:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, we are happy to see our code can be used in the future HBase releases (if possible). For integration what kind of work there will be? Currently, we don&apos;t have concrete plan or experience on it yet. But will happy to initiate and help in this process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, the current project is mainly implemented as extended library on the client side and coprocessor on the server side. In other words, it does not change existing HBase codebase. In this case, does it make sense to make patch? If yes, how to patch (treat me as a newbie on that)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14521978" author="elserj" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 18:16:13 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;In other words, it does not change existing HBase codebase. In this case, does it make sense to make patch?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO, I think it&apos;s easier to keep this external to HBase. It&apos;s already hard enough to write and maintain the primitives in a key-value store that your project uses. Also, since your project is already cleanly separated into using the expected client-facing code HBase provides, I don&apos;t much immediate value in pulling it into HBase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you do really want to include this in HBase itself, it would be good to outline answers to some basic where/why/how questions (e.g. where does this fit into HBase itself? why should it be included in HBase? how would you technically go about including it?). If the community can come to agreement that it would be a worthwhile endeavor to pursue, only then would it make sense to do start investigating the necessary incubator/code-grant steps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
